         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 4 Aug. 1891. ¶ To the honorable ¶ Sir Henry Parkes, G.C.M.G. ¶ Premier of NSW &amp;c &amp;c...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.08.04a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Parkes</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A893 Parkes correspondence, vol. 23, pp. 454-6, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4 Aug. 1891.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">To the honorable</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir Henry Parkes, G.C.M.G.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Premier of NSW &amp;c &amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is with profound feelings of gratitude, dear Sir Henry, that I learnt from Mr Wolff, how generously you were inclined towards the forthcoming Swedish-Australian Expediton to the south-polar regions, in promising to ask the Parliament of your great colony to vote fully £2000 for this important enterprise, and in your deciding to bring this proposition very early before the legislative Assembly there.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to P. Wolff, 29 July 1891.</p>
               </note> Not only is your enlightenedness to be recognized as a sentiment representative of New South Wales, but it will also have the effect of accelerating the aid of those Australian Governments, which as yet have the claims for such a grand science-exploration and for such a promising access to Australian industrial developments under consideration in a truely federal spirit.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the deepest gratitude and with the best expressions of regard,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain, dear Sir Henry,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
